cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper is about Programming-by-Example (PBE) systems, which are used to synthesize programs from input-output examples. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the use of quantitative cost functions, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents a modular approach for solving the problem, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the experiments involve a large number of benchmarks, which suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB).
